MBAISE – The chairman of Aboh Mbaise Local Government Council in Imo State, Mr. Emma Njoku, has assured the people of Uvuru of his readiness to make government’s presence to be felt in the area. The council chairman made the promise on Friday when he received the Executive Committee of Uvuru Communities Development Union (UCDU) led by the President-General, Mr. Chimaroke Ben Nnaji.Njoku was delighted that the UCDU executives paid him a visit and thanked them for the gesture.Earlier, Nnaji had assured the Aboh Mbaise council boss of Uvuru people’s support for his administration.He thanked Njoku for the ongoing intervention at Orie Uvuru Market and urged him to see to its successful completion.The UCDU delegation included Chief Goddy Madugba, Nze Ben Otti, Mr. Peter Claver Nwaiwu, Mr Kennedy Nnaji, Mr Eze Imoh, Chief Linus Ibeh and Chief Monday Odoemena.  •Mr. Chimaroke Nnaji (right), the new President-General of Uvuru Community Development Union (UCDU) being declared elected on 2 January 2022 at Central School, Uvuru, Mbaise, by Chief Nwabueze Njoku, the immediate past President-General of UCDU.... UVURU, Mbaise, Imo State - (Sundiata Post) - The new President-General of Uvuru Community Development… In "Metro" •Sir Stanley Amuchie, Executive Director, Fidelity Bank By CHIBUIKE NWABUKO Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The entire people of Uvuru Ikedinairi in Aboh Mbaise LGA, Imo State, have hailed Fidelity Bank PLC for the appointment of one of their sons, Sir Stanley Chiedozie Amuchie as Executive Director, Chief Operations and Information… In "Top Stories" UVURU, Imo State - Traditional rulers and religious leaders in Uvuru community in the Aboh Mbaise Local Government Area of Imo State will on Saturday, September 8, converge for a prayer and blessing session for Sir Stanley Amuchie, a general manager, Zenith Bank Plc. Sir Stanley, a frontline governorship aspirant… In "News"